{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WFcvv5tmWJWwMnf6dvtR1J","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `rollback-rehearsal` ConfigMap is stored and the live cluster is untouched (all 3 pods still running with 0 restarts).\n\n---\n\n**What was found and what the script does:**\n\nThe four non-default settings identified (from `mongod-config` ConfigMap + `getCmdLineOpts`):\n\n| Setting | Live value | MongoDB default |\n|---|---|---|\n| `systemLog.verbosity` | 1 | 0 |\n| `operationProfiling.mode` | `slowOp` | `off` |\n| `operationProfiling.slowOpThresholdMs` | 200 ms | 100 ms |\n| `storage.wiredTiger.engineConfig.journalCompressor` | `zlib` | `snappy` |\n\nThe `rollback.sh` script (stored under the `rollback.sh` key) executes in three phases:\n\n1. **Live `setParameter` resets** — calls `setParameter logComponentVerbosity` and `profile 0, slowms 100` on every member; takes effect immediately without a restart.\n2. **ConfigMap patch** — rewrites `mongod-config` to remove the `systemLog` and `operationProfiling` sections and switches `journalCompressor` back to `snappy`.\n3. **Rolling restart** — deletes and waits for each pod (secondaries first, then primary), so every node reloads the config file. This is required for the `journalCompressor` change to take effect, since WiredTiger reads that setting only at startup.\n\n**Not reverted:** `security.authorization`/`keyFile` and the `admin-user` account — removing auth infra while auth is enabled would immediately lock out all clients."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":167,"cache_read_input_tokens":44052,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":167},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c602bfc7-b178-4552-8f26-fd2cfb1